  "verdict": "Paper 1's 2-D a-posteriori null is the inverse cascade. In 2-D the spectral energy flux is negative just below the forcing (energy goes UP-scale; band min -1.00), so the resolved scales carry NO net forward energy flux to the subgrid: the forward part of <Pi>/sigma is 0.0059 (<=0.01) at every cutoff around k_f (primary kc=32: mu/sigma=+0.0011, nu_opt=+8.52e-08). A positive-definite eddy viscosity has nothing to represent, so it cannot beat no-model. In 3-D the cascade is forward (live CPU mu/sigma=+0.0351>0, nu_opt=+4.80e-05>0; the six committed P100 runs give mu/sigma in [0.039, 0.099], all positive, the NR29 sign), so the optimal eddy viscosity is positive (budget argmin 4.80e-05>0) and a positive/structural closure strictly beats no-model. The null is a prediction of 2-D physics; it predicts the decisive 3-D a-posteriori ordering of Paper 1 sec 8.1.",
